    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>In postclassic central Mexico, a Mexica military commander whose role is both to start the war and to lead the fight. Associated with the Tlacateccatl warrior and more generally with Huitzilopochtli.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000320/GRI-FloCo</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000109721/GRI, FloCo terminology (2019-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>En el México central posclásico, un comandante militar cuyo papel es tanto iniciar la guerra como dirigir la lucha. Asociado con el guerrero Tlacateccatl y más generalmente con Huitzilopochtli.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000320/GRI-FloCo</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000109721/GRI, FloCo terminology (2019-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Pan Mexco central posclásico, ce comandante militar tlen itequiuh quipehualtiz tlahuilantli quence ce tlayecanquetl. Tlen mozancehcotlaltoc huanya ce tlahuilanquetl Tlacateccatl huan nochipa huanya Huitzilopochtli.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Eastern Huasteca Nahuatl</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000320/GRI-FloCo</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
